#. <section class="sutta" id="sn15.13"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn15.13:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 15"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 15"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn15.13:0.2"
msgid "2. Dutiyavagga"
msgstr "2. The Second Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn15.13:0.3"
msgid "13. Tiṃsamattasutta"
msgstr "13. Thirty Mendicants"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn15.13:1.1"
msgid "Rājagahe viharati veḷuvane."
msgstr "Near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove."

#. VAR: pāveyyakā → pāṭheyyakā (si) | paveyyakā (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn15.13:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho tiṃsamattā pāveyyakā bhikkhū sabbe āraññikā sabbe piṇḍapātikā sabbe "
"paṃsukūlikā sabbe tecīvarikā sabbe sasaṃyojanā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
" upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Then thirty mendicants from Pāvā went to the Buddha. All of them lived in "
"the wilderness, ate only alms-food, wore rag robes, and owned just three "
"robes; yet they all still had fetters. They bowed to the Buddha and sat down "
"to one side."

msgctxt "sn15.13:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavato etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn15.13:1.4"
msgid ""
"“ime kho tiṃsamattā pāveyyakā bhikkhū sabbe āraññikā sabbe piṇḍapātikā sabbe "
"paṃsukūlikā sabbe tecīvarikā sabbe sasaṃyojanā."
msgstr ""
"“These thirty mendicants from Pāvā live in the wilderness, eat only alms-"
"food, wear rag robes, and own just three robes; yet they all still have "
"fetters."

msgctxt "sn15.13:1.5"
msgid ""
"Yannūnāhaṃ imesaṃ tathā dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ yathā nesaṃ imasmiṃyeva āsane "
"anupādāya āsavehi cittāni vimucceyyun”ti."
msgstr ""
"Why don’t I teach them the Dhamma in such a way that their minds are freed "
"from defilements by not grasping while sitting in this very seat?”"

msgctxt "sn15.13:1.6"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to the mendicants:"

msgctxt "sn15.13:1.7"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "sn15.13:1.8"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "sn15.13:1.9"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.188"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn15.13:2.1"
msgid "“Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro."
msgstr "“Mendicants, transmigration has no known beginning."

msgctxt "sn15.13:2.2"
msgid ""
"Pubbā koṭi na paññāyati avijjānīvaraṇānaṃ sattānaṃ taṇhāsaṃyojanānaṃ "
"sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ."
msgstr ""
"No first point is found of sentient beings roaming and transmigrating, "
"hindered by ignorance and fettered by craving."

msgctxt "sn15.13:2.3"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, katamaṃ nu kho bahutaraṃ, yaṃ vā vo iminā "
"dīghena addhunā sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ sīsacchinnānaṃ lohitaṃ passannaṃ "
"paggharitaṃ, yaṃ vā catūsu mahāsamuddesu udakan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"What do you think? Which is more: the flow of blood you’ve shed when your "
"head was chopped off while roaming and transmigrating for such a very long "
"time, or the water in the four oceans?”"

msgctxt "sn15.13:2.4"
msgid ""
"“Yathā kho mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāma, etadeva, "
"bhante, bahutaraṃ, yaṃ no iminā dīghena addhunā sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ "
"sīsacchinnānaṃ lohitaṃ passannaṃ paggharitaṃ, na tveva catūsu mahāsamuddesu "
"udakan”ti."
msgstr ""
"“As we understand the Buddha’s teaching, the flow of blood we’ve shed when "
"our head was chopped off while roaming and transmigrating is more than the "
"water in the four oceans.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn15.13:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Sādhu sādhu, bhikkhave, sādhu kho me tumhe, bhikkhave, evaṃ dhammaṃ desitaṃ "
"ājānātha."
msgstr ""
"“Good, good, mendicants! It’s good that you understand my teaching like this."

msgctxt "sn15.13:3.2"
msgid ""
"Etadeva, bhikkhave, bahutaraṃ, yaṃ vo iminā dīghena addhunā sandhāvataṃ "
"saṃsarataṃ sīsacchinnānaṃ lohitaṃ passannaṃ paggharitaṃ, na tveva catūsu "
"mahāsamuddesu udakaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The flow of blood you’ve shed when your head was chopped off while roaming "
"and transmigrating is indeed more than the water in the four oceans."

msgctxt "sn15.13:3.3"
msgid ""
"Dīgharattaṃ vo, bhikkhave, gunnaṃ sataṃ gobhūtānaṃ sīsacchinnānaṃ lohitaṃ "
"passannaṃ paggharitaṃ, na tveva catūsu mahāsamuddesu udakaṃ."
msgstr ""
"For a long time you’ve been cows, and the flow of blood you’ve shed when "
"your head was chopped off as a cow is more than the water in the four oceans."

#. VAR: mahiṃsānaṃ → mahisānaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1-2, mr)
msgctxt "sn15.13:3.4"
msgid ""
"Dīgharattaṃ vo, bhikkhave, mahiṃsānaṃ sataṃ mahiṃsabhūtānaṃ sīsacchinnānaṃ "
"lohitaṃ passannaṃ paggharitaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "For a long time you’ve been buffalo …"

# Not sure why BB has sheep here. CPD only gives rams.
msgctxt "sn15.13:3.5"
msgid "dīgharattaṃ vo, bhikkhave, urabbhānaṃ sataṃ urabbhabhūtānaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "rams …"

msgctxt "sn15.13:3.6"
msgid "ajānaṃ sataṃ ajabhūtānaṃ …"
msgstr "goats …"

msgctxt "sn15.13:3.7"
msgid "migānaṃ sataṃ migabhūtānaṃ …"
msgstr "deer …"

msgctxt "sn15.13:3.8"
msgid "kukkuṭānaṃ sataṃ kukkuṭabhūtānaṃ …"
msgstr "chickens …"

msgctxt "sn15.13:3.9"
msgid "sūkarānaṃ sataṃ sūkarabhūtānaṃ …"
msgstr "pigs …"

# BB has “burglary”, which is surely too weak. ghata is to kill, destroy, attack. generally the idea of cora is not really our modern “thief”, more like an outlaw or bandit. They probably raided villages, killed, raped, and plundered.
msgctxt "sn15.13:3.10"
msgid ""
"dīgharattaṃ vo, bhikkhave, corā gāmaghātāti gahetvā sīsacchinnānaṃ lohitaṃ "
"passannaṃ paggharitaṃ."
msgstr "For a long time you’ve been bandits, arrested for raiding villages,"

msgctxt "sn15.13:3.11"
msgid ""
"Dīgharattaṃ vo, bhikkhave, corā pāripanthikāti gahetvā sīsacchinnānaṃ "
"lohitaṃ passannaṃ paggharitaṃ."
msgstr "highway robbery,"

# I can’t help feeling that something stronger is required here for paradarika, i.e rape. But I can’t find any contexts that clarify whether consent was an issue in this crime.
msgctxt "sn15.13:3.12"
msgid ""
"Dīgharattaṃ vo, bhikkhave, corā pāradārikāti gahetvā sīsacchinnānaṃ lohitaṃ "
"passannaṃ paggharitaṃ, na tveva catūsu mahāsamuddesu udakaṃ."
msgstr ""
"or adultery. And the flow of blood you’ve shed when your head was chopped "
"off as a bandit is more than the water in the four oceans."

msgctxt "sn15.13:3.13"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn15.13:3.14"
msgid "Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro … pe …"
msgstr "Transmigration has no known beginning. …"

msgctxt "sn15.13:3.15"
msgid "alaṃ vimuccitun”ti."
msgstr ""
"This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and "
"freed regarding all conditions.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.189"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn15.13:4.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "sn15.13:4.2"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti."
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "sn15.13:4.3"
msgid ""
"Imasmiñca pana veyyākaraṇasmiṃ bhaññamāne tiṃsamattānaṃ pāveyyakānaṃ "
"bhikkhūnaṃ anupādāya āsavehi cittāni vimucciṃsūti."
msgstr ""
"And while this discourse was being spoken, the minds of the thirty "
"mendicants from Pāvā were freed from defilements by not grasping."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn15.13:4.4"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
